ential violations. I wonder if reflection is acceptable since it seems to fit the dynamic loading pattern, but I need to ensure it complies with guidelines. I’ll confirm the code compiles correctly and check for any necessary dependencies like NativeImageSupport. Will this cover everything I need?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating factory behavior**\\n\\nI’m trying to understand why the class static field in the child factory is null when `createParams` is invoked. It seems the verifier might resolve `SimpleHttpConnectionManager` beforehand, but the bytecode uses a synthetic approach instead of the expected constant. Despite the attempts, the dynamic report after the second build still shows nothing. It could be that the test didn't run correctly since the field was already set, and using a fresh loader might help. I really need to clarify the line length issue too!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_lhkYImpqncC5zFa5me3xs8rm|fc_050a331f00a2d90c016a04aed5b400819e95832418cb24995e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path('tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/src/test/java/commons_httpclient/commons_httpclient/DefaultHttpParamsFactoryTest.java')\nfor i,l in enumerate(p.read_text().splitlines(),1):\n    if len(l)>100:\n        print(i,len(l),l)\nPY", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 826, "output": 1096, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44930, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778691776675, "responseId": "resp_050a331f00a2d90c016a04aec1f910819e83344861f153b5e1"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_lhkYImpqncC5zFa5me3xs8rm|fc_050a331f00a2d90c016a04aed5b400819e95832418cb24995e", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "62 106         try (DefaultHttpParamsFactoryCla